After nearly 200 emails to professors and labs, and after applying to nearly 3 international internship programs. Around 12PM
on 22nd January 2019, an Email from a professor who I had been interviewing at GeorgiaTech for nearly 3 months wrote back to me
saying "Congratulations for being selected as an intern in Summer 2019 at Georgia Tech". Ofcourse I was running all around my 
campus in excitment, went out with people for lunch and did a lot of partying! Fast forward 2 months I was busy getting my paper
work done for a J1 visa (Will have a separate blog on how to go about this process). After a lot of hassle with the visa process
I finally made it to Atlanta on 15th June 2019 to work at the "AI and Transportation lab" at GeorgiaTech.

GeorgiaTech is world leader in research and has some of the leading professors in the verticals of Computer Vision and AI.
Cracking an Intern at GerogiaTech, was not something done overnight, one email or one interview. Right from drafting the initial
email, clearing 3 coding assignments and 2 telephonic interviews, I was on constantly aleat and solved the assignments with atmost 
care. 
